---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Work Visa Comparison | Compare Work Permits Worldwide"
description: "Compare work visa requirements, processing times, salary thresholds, and paths to permanent residence across 9 countries. EU Blue Card vs UK Skilled Worker vs H-1B and more."
---

{% block structuredData %}
<script type="application/ld+json">
{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@graph": [
    {
      "@type": "WebApplication",
      "name": "Work Visa Comparison Tool",
      "url": "{{ site.url }}/tools/visa-comparison/",
      "description": "{{ description }}",
      "applicationCategory": "ReferenceApplication",
      "operatingSystem": "Any",
      "offers": { "@type": "Offer", "price": "0", "priceCurrency": "EUR" },
      "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "{{ site.name }}", "url": "{{ site.url }}" }
    },
    {
      "@type": "FAQPage",
      "mainEntity": [
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Which work visa is easiest to get?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "The Netherlands Highly Skilled Migrant (HSM) visa is often considered the easiest to obtain for tech workers. It has the fastest processing time (2-4 weeks), no language requirement, no labor market test, and no lottery system. The EU Blue Card (Germany) and Canada Global Talent Stream are also relatively straightforward if you meet the salary threshold."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Which work visa has the fastest processing time?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "The Canada Global Talent Stream targets 2-week processing, making it the fastest work visa program. The Netherlands HSM visa (2-4 weeks) and France Passeport Talent (2-6 weeks) are also very fast. For premium processing, the US H-1B offers 15-day processing for an additional fee."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Which visa offers the fastest path to permanent residence?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "The EU Blue Card (Germany) offers the fastest path to permanent residence — just 21 months if you have B1 German language skills, or 33 months without. Ireland's Critical Skills Permit leads to unrestricted Stamp 4 in just 2 years. Canada's Express Entry can grant permanent residence in 6-12 months after obtaining a work permit."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Do all work visas allow my spouse to work?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Most modern work visa programs allow spouses to work. The EU Blue Card, UK Skilled Worker, Netherlands HSM, and Australia TSS all grant full work rights to spouses. The US H-1B is the notable exception — spouses on H-4 visas can only work if the H-1B holder has an approved I-140 petition, which typically takes years."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "Is there a lottery for work visas?",
          "acceptedAnswer": {
            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "The US H-1B is the only major work visa that requires a lottery. With approximately 25% selection rate and an annual cap of 85,000 visas, it's the most uncertain path. All other major work visas (EU Blue Card, UK Skilled Worker, Netherlands HSM, Canada GTS, Australia TSS, etc.) are deterministic — if you meet the requirements, you get the visa."
          }
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
</script>
{% endblock %}

<section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-50 via-white to-sky-50 dark:from-gray-950 dark:via-gray-900 dark:to-gray-950 py-16">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
    <nav class="flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">
      <a href="/" class="hover:text-brand-600 dark:hover:text-brand-400">Home</a>
      <i data-lucide="chevron-right" class="w-4 h-4"></i>
      <span class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">Tools</span>
      <i data-lucide="chevron-right" class="w-4 h-4"></i>
      <span class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Visa Comparison</span>
    </nav>
    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
      <div class="w-14 h-14 bg-sky-100 dark:bg-sky-900/30 rounded-2xl flex items-center justify-center">
        <i data-lucide="scale" class="w-7 h-7 text-sky-600 dark:text-sky-400"></i>
      </div>
      <div>
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Work Visa Comparison</h1>
        <p class="text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 mt-1">Compare work permits across 9 countries side-by-side</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 max-w-3xl mb-8">
      EU Blue Card vs UK Skilled Worker vs H-1B — which visa is right for you? Sort, filter, and compare processing times, salary thresholds, spouse work rights, and paths to permanent residence.
    </p>

    {# Filters #}
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mb-4">
      <div>
        <label for="filter-country" class="sr-only">Filter by country</label>
        <select id="filter-country" class="input-field text-sm py-2">
          <option value="">All Countries</option>
          {% set countrySet = [] %}
          {% for visa in visaTypes %}
            {% if visa.country not in countrySet %}
              {% set countrySet = (countrySet.push(visa.country), countrySet) %}
              <option value="{{ visa.country }}">{{ visa.country }}</option>
            {% endif %}
          {% endfor %}
        </select>
      </div>
      <div>
        <label for="filter-speed" class="sr-only">Processing speed</label>
        <select id="filter-speed" class="input-field text-sm py-2">
          <option value="">All Processing Speeds</option>
          <option value="fast">Fast (under 4 weeks)</option>
          <option value="medium">Medium (4-8 weeks)</option>
          <option value="slow">Slow (2+ months)</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      <div>
        <label for="filter-spouse" class="sr-only">Spouse work rights</label>
        <select id="filter-spouse" class="input-field text-sm py-2">
          <option value="">Spouse Work Rights</option>
          <option value="yes">Unrestricted</option>
          <option value="limited">Limited / Conditional</option>
        </select>
      </div>
      <button id="clear-filters" class="btn-secondary text-sm py-2 hidden">
        <i data-lucide="x" class="w-4 h-4 mr-1"></i> Clear Filters
      </button>
    </div>

    {# Compare mode #}
    <div id="compare-bar" class="hidden sticky top-16 z-30 bg-brand-600 dark:bg-brand-700 text-white rounded-xl p-4 mb-4 flex items-center justify-between shadow-lg">
      <div class="flex items-center gap-2">
        <i data-lucide="git-compare" class="w-5 h-5"></i>
        <span id="compare-count">0</span> visas selected for comparison
      </div>
      <div class="flex gap-2">
        <button id="compare-btn" class="px-4 py-2 bg-white text-brand-600 font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-brand-50 transition-colors text-sm">Compare Now</button>
        <button id="clear-compare" class="px-4 py-2 bg-brand-500 rounded-lg hover:bg-brand-400 transition-colors text-sm">Clear</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{# Table #}
<section class="py-8">
  <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4">
    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-left" id="visa-table">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
            <th class="p-3 w-10">
              <span class="sr-only">Compare</span>
            </th>
            <th class="p-3 font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white cursor-pointer hover:text-brand-600 dark:hover:text-brand-400 transition-colors sortable whitespace-nowrap" data-sort="name">
              Visa Name <i data-lucide="arrow-up-down" class="w-4 h-4 inline ml-1 opacity-40"></i>
            </th>
            <th class="p-3 font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white cursor-pointer hover:text-brand-600 dark:hover:text-brand-400 transition-colors sortable whitespace-nowrap" data-sort="country">
              Country <i data-lucide="arrow-up-down" class="w-4 h-4 inline ml-1 opacity-40"></i>
            </th>
            <th class="p-3 font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white cursor-pointer hover:text-brand-600 dark:hover:text-brand-400 transition-colors sortable whitespace-nowrap" data-sort="processing">
              Processing <i data-lucide="arrow-up-down" class="w-4 h-4 inline ml-1 opacity-40"></i>
            </th>
            <th class="p-3 font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white cursor-pointer hover:text-brand-600 dark:hover:text-brand-400 transition-colors sortable whitespace-nowrap" data-sort="salary">
              Salary Threshold <i data-lucide="arrow-up-down" class="w-4 h-4 inline ml-1 opacity-40"></i>
            </th>
            <th class="p-3 font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white whitespace-nowrap">Spouse Work</th>
            <th class="p-3 font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white whitespace-nowrap">Path to PR</th>
            <th class="p-3 font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white whitespace-nowrap">Lottery</th>
            <th class="p-3 w-10"><span class="sr-only">Expand</span></th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody id="visa-tbody">
          {% for visa in visaTypes %}
          <tr class="visa-row border-b border-gray-100 dark:border-gray-800 hover:bg-gray-50 dark:hover:bg-gray-800/50 transition-colors"
              data-slug="{{ visa.slug }}"
              data-country="{{ visa.country }}"
              data-processing="{{ visa.processingTime }}"
              data-spouse="{{ visa.spouseWork }}"
              data-salary="{{ visa.salaryThreshold }}"
              data-lottery="{{ visa.lottery }}">
            <td class="p-3">
              <input type="checkbox" class="compare-check w-4 h-4 rounded border-gray-300 text-brand-600 focus:ring-brand-500" data-slug="{{ visa.slug }}">
            </td>
            <td class="p-3">
              <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white">{{ visa.name }}</span>
              <span class="block text-xs text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">{{ visa.category }}</span>
            </td>
            <td class="p-3 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">{{ visa.country }}</td>
            <td class="p-3">
              {% set ptime = visa.processingTime %}
              {% if "2 week" in ptime or "2-4 week" in ptime or "2-6 week" in ptime %}
                <span class="badge" style="background:rgb(220 252 231);color:rgb(22 101 52)">{{ ptime }}</span>
              {% elif "3-6 month" in ptime or "1-4 month" in ptime %}
                <span class="badge" style="background:rgb(254 243 199);color:rgb(146 64 14)">{{ ptime }}</span>
              {% else %}
                <span class="badge" style="background:rgb(219 234 254);color:rgb(30 64 175)">{{ ptime }}</span>
              {% endif %}
            </td>
            <td class="p-3 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">{{ visa.salaryThreshold }}</td>
            <td class="p-3">
              {% if "unrestricted" in visa.spouseWork.toLowerCase() or "Yes, unrestricted" in visa.spouseWork or "Yes, full" in visa.spouseWork or "automatic" in visa.spouseWork.toLowerCase() %}
                <span class="text-emerald-600 dark:text-emerald-400 flex items-center gap-1 text-sm"><i data-lucide="check-circle" class="w-4 h-4"></i> Yes</span>
              {% elif "Yes" in visa.spouseWork %}
                <span class="text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 flex items-center gap-1 text-sm"><i data-lucide="check-circle" class="w-4 h-4"></i> Conditional</span>
              {% else %}
                <span class="text-red-600 dark:text-red-400 flex items-center gap-1 text-sm"><i data-lucide="x-circle" class="w-4 h-4"></i> Limited</span>
              {% endif %}
            </td>
            <td class="p-3 text-sm text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">{{ visa.pathToPR }}</td>
            <td class="p-3">
              {% if visa.lottery %}
                <span class="badge" style="background:rgb(254 226 226);color:rgb(153 27 27)">Yes</span>
              {% else %}
                <span class="badge" style="background:rgb(220 252 231);color:rgb(22 101 52)">No</span>
              {% endif %}
            </td>
            <td class="p-3">
              <button class="expand-btn p-1 rounded hover:bg-gray-200 dark:hover:bg-gray-700 transition-colors" data-slug="{{ visa.slug }}">
                <i data-lucide="chevron-down" class="w-5 h-5 text-gray-400 expand-icon transition-transform duration-200"></i>
              </button>
            </td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="visa-detail hidden" data-detail="{{ visa.slug }}">
            <td colspan="9" class="p-0">
              <div class="p-6 bg-gray-50 dark:bg-gray-800/50 border-b border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2 flex items-center gap-2"><i data-lucide="list-checks" class="w-4 h-4 text-brand-500"></i> Requirements</h4>
                    <ul class="space-y-1">
                      {% for req in visa.requirements %}
                      <li class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 flex items-start gap-2">
                        <i data-lucide="check" class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-emerald-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5"></i>
                        {{ req }}
                      </li>
                      {% endfor %}
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2 flex items-center gap-2"><i data-lucide="thumbs-up" class="w-4 h-4 text-emerald-500"></i> Pros</h4>
                    <ul class="space-y-1">
                      {% for pro in visa.pros %}
                      <li class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 flex items-start gap-2">
                        <i data-lucide="plus" class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-emerald-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5"></i>
                        {{ pro }}
                      </li>
                      {% endfor %}
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                  <div>
                    <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2 flex items-center gap-2"><i data-lucide="thumbs-down" class="w-4 h-4 text-red-500"></i> Cons</h4>
                    <ul class="space-y-1">
                      {% for con in visa.cons %}
                      <li class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 flex items-start gap-2">
                        <i data-lucide="minus" class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-red-500 shrink-0 mt-0.5"></i>
                        {{ con }}
                      </li>
                      {% endfor %}
                    </ul>
                  </div>
                </div>
                <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3 mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">
                  <span class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400"><strong>Validity:</strong> {{ visa.validity }}</span>
                  <span class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">|</span>
                  <span class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400"><strong>Spouse:</strong> {{ visa.spouseWork }}</span>
                </div>
                <div class="flex gap-3 mt-4">
                  <a href="{{ visa.officialUrl }}" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="btn-primary text-sm">
                    <i data-lucide="external-link" class="w-4 h-4 mr-1"></i> Official Page
                  </a>
                  <a href="/visa-sponsored-jobs/" class="btn-secondary text-sm">
                    <i data-lucide="briefcase" class="w-4 h-4 mr-1"></i> Find Jobs
                  </a>
                </div>
              </div>
            </td>
          </tr>
          {% endfor %}
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    {# Comparison panel #}
    <div id="compare-panel" class="hidden mt-8">
      <div class="card p-6 md:p-8">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-6">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white flex items-center gap-2">
            <i data-lucide="git-compare" class="w-5 h-5 text-brand-600 dark:text-brand-400"></i>
            Side-by-Side Comparison
          </h2>
          <button id="close-compare" class="btn-secondary text-sm"><i data-lucide="x" class="w-4 h-4 mr-1"></i> Close</button>
        </div>
        <div id="compare-content" class="overflow-x-auto"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

